<subSubSection id="CA1CF3703F903519C85C88568FFEF5E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="169B7CC51ED85E85EDADD690543A5A8F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E0D1B00AB8CC404D2E7D16C247A6D7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Endemic to Mexico growing at around 800-1000 m in semi-deciduous forest.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A54BBE5AB36CA24595709D40A4186C79" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="E4894FA9F49193B819EBF7E632122CEE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">MEXICO. Guerrero</emphasis>
: type locality. 
<emphasis id="E5F6CE1BAFE7F18F533D9E6BFDABA254" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Jalisco</emphasis>
: Mun. El Limon, Cerro el Carrizal, 
<emphasis id="6E2C58B5118BF3AA442063CA8709E87B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Flores</emphasis>
3679 (MEXU).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FD319C2C78FD769C95EEF09B1E666CE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="CF21EC97F4D1A18F31F3DD2A79B571D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A5248048EAECA3AF49A651BD27C86894" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Very distinctive because of the setose peduncles and the disc-like receptacle. The peduncles, pedicels and sepals are reported to be sticky glandular. The annual habit combined with the hypocrateriform white corolla is also unusual.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
